This paper is about training neural network-based models for natural language generation tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of regularization methods to address the representation degeneration problem, which is a common issue in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method to address this problem, which involves modifying the training process of the neural network, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of the representation degeneration problem on language modeling and machine translation, which are both subfields of natural language processing (NLP) that are closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
